You're right. Let me look more carefully at the error and the code.

The error is "Conversion failed when converting the nvarchar val" at line 214 in PS_generate. Looking at PS_generate.sql, line 214 is around where it calls PS_DCS_run with @calc_list.

The issue might be in how the calc_list is being parsed. When calc_list contains comma-separated IDs, somewhere in the code it's trying to convert these to integers. If there's any non-numeric value, whitespace, or formatting issue in the calc_list string, the conversion will fail.

Looking at your calc_list, I notice it might have HTML entities like `&#39;` (which is a single quote). The error message you showed has `&#39;` in several places:

```
@user_id=&#39;admin&#39;
@calc_list=&#39;8986,8984,8982...
```

This suggests the calc_list string might contain `&#39;` characters instead of actual single quotes, or there might be other HTML-encoded characters in the string that are causing the conversion to fail when the procedure tries to parse the comma-separated integers.

Check if your calc_list parameter has any HTML-encoded characters or extra whitespace that would prevent proper integer conversion.

